<SLUG> BC-NY-HEALTH-PLAN-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BENEFITS FOR BUSINESSES AND FAMILIES 
</HEADLINE>
   (Eds: With related NY-TOBACCO-TAX and NY-TOBACCO-INDUSTRY
articles) 
(af)  
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Following are highlights of the proposed ``Healthy New York''
package: &QL;
</P>
<P>
   SMALL BUSINESSES: Offers state subsidies to make insurance
premiums more affordable for businesses with 50 or fewer employees.
The standard benefits will include hospital services, X-ray and
laboratory services, maternity care and prescription drugs.
</P>
<P>
   FAMILIES: Extends state subsidies to members of some uninsured
families who do not get health insurance through their employers.
</P>
<P>
   TOBACCO TAX: Increases the tax on cigarettes by 55 cents to
raise an estimated $400 million a year for the new health care
plan.
</P>
<P>
   MEDICAID: Extends for three years $1 billion in previously
approved cuts that are set to expire in April. In exchange, the
governor agrees not to propose any new cuts in Medicaid for up to
three years.
</P>
<P>
   HOSPITAL AID: Renews a program that pays hospitals billions of
dollars a year to provide a range of services.
</P>
</TEXT>
