<HEADER>
A2581 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r e BC-FANTASIA-2000-LADN     12-18 0384
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FANTASIA-2000-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DISNEY LETS MOUSE OUT OF BAG ON WIDE RELEASE OF `FANTASIA'
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By Dave McNary  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Walt Disney Co. has confirmed it will release
``Fantasia 2000'' next year in the regular 35 millimeter format
after its exclusive four-month run at 71 large-format Imax sites.
</P>
<P>
   Burbank-based Disney had been vague about whether it would move
the update of the animated classic, which will open on New Year's
Day, into conventional theaters. But its holiday card _ sent this
week to thousands of friends, associates and vendors of the
entertainment conglomerate _ spilled the beans by listing a July
opening as part of its key ``Disney dates'' for the upcoming year.
</P>
<P>
   Distribution chief Chuck Viane admitted that the film, featuring
seven new sequences plus ``The Sorcerer's Apprentice'' from the
1940 original, will receive a nationwide rollout sometime next year
but added that July is not necessarily when it will open. ``We will
definitely have a 35 mm break for the film but it's a little
premature to say what the date is,'' he added.
</P>
<P>
   Chances are good that the opening date for ``Fantasia 2000''
will not be in May, since Disney has already set May 12 for
``Dinosaur,'' a high-cost project with leading-edge animation and
one of its ``tentpole'' releases for the summer season. Trailers
for ``Dinosaur,'' which appears aimed squarely at children and
families, were launched last month along with the opening of ``Toy
Story 2.''
</P>
<P>
   Entertainment analyst Kevin Skoslock of Laguna Research Partners
said it makes sense for Disney to keep its strategy undercover.
``It's smart of them to leave themselves some flexibility in
scheduling,'' he added. ``I've got a feeling that this is going be
a strong performer, so it would not surprise me if they extended
the Imax run.''
</P>
<P>
   Disney has booked Southern California screenings for ``Fantasia
2000'' at Imax theaters in Valencia, Irvine, Cathedral City and
Ontario. It is also building a 622-seat temporary theater in the
Westchester area that will be dismantled once the Imax run is
completed.
</P>
<P>
   ``The fact that Disney is building a temporary theater sends a
signal that they may have a hit,'' Skoslock noted.
</P>
<P>
   X X X  &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-12-18-99 0116EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19991218.0037 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
