   GLOBAL-WARMING _ Last month was the warmest November in 105
years of record-keeping in the contiguous 48 states, and the
fourth-warmest in the Northeast. The trend continued into December
in most of the country; as of Friday, the average temperature for
the month in New York, for example, was 5.7 degrees Fahrenheit
above normal. But that is almost the least of it. Federal
scientists reported last week that in the contiguous 48 states and
on other global land masses, 1999 is certain to join 1998 as one of
the two warmest years on record, continuing a long-term trend
toward a warmer climate. By William K. Stevens.
