   Yet for all its mystique and undisputed national stature, Texas
actually has one of the weakest gubernatorial offices in the
country, a legacy of a Reconstruction-era constitution that was
written to curb executive power.
</P>
<P>
   According to political scientists, Texas stands anywhere from
