   DOG-FIGHTING _ It's called a blood sport. But when police raided
a dogfight in southeast Georgia's Wayne County, what officers found
was more like a bloodletting. The raid highlighted the popularity
of dogfighting in rural Georgia, where it has been a macabre
tradition for generations. But dogfighting has become more than a
rural pastime. In Georgia and across the country, police say, it is
an increasingly common hobby in urban neighborhoods, especially
among members of street gangs. (Judd, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
WITH PHOTOS.
