   Y2K-ALLYEAR _ Less than two weeks from the world's date with
computer destiny, it's hard to find anyone _ even among the
original prophets of Y2K doom _ who expects a midnight meltdown
when 1999 rolls over to 2000. But while New Year's weekend should
pass without cyber-cataclysm, experts say low-grade inconveniences
related to Y2K could persist for weeks or months. (Bennett, Palm
Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   SAMS-SONG _ Sam Taylor is a 40-year-old autistic struggling to
be normal in a world that is just out of his grasp. We witness his
struggle _ his small victories as well as his failures _ as he
comes to accept his lot. From a musical family, music soothes his
tormented mind in a special way. He eventually gets a job at the
Atlanta Symphony sorting tickets and subscribers. (Dyer, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 100. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
