   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Sunday, Dec. 19. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
MAY-RESERVE _ Steve May wants to be known as a serious legislator,
not the Rosa Parks of gays in the military. ``I think my
constituents are tired of hearing about my private life. I am tired
of talking about it,'' said May, whose public admission about being
gay has triggering an investigation that threatens to end his
career in the Army Reserve. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
NET-RURAL _ It's the great promise of the Internet: For 20 bucks a
month and a local phone line, the world is yours. Plug in, dial up
and click _ you're surfing across continents, fetching information
from faraway capitals, chatting up cyberpals in London, Tokyo,
Buenos Aires . . . Anywhere but Wickenburg and other remote places
in Arizona. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
