<HEADLINE>
HITTING THE BOOKS  
 A MILESTONE FOR GREEN
</HEADLINE>
   (rk) 
 By MIKE FREEMAN   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Professional football players are going back to school in record
numbers, and some are even taking graduate courses. This fall, 13
players are taking courses to finish undergraduate degrees or have
started graduate work as part of the league's continuing education
program.
</P>
<P>
   When the program began in 1991, 141 players and spouses were
enrolled. This past year, 455 people were part of the program. The
NFL picks up all or a portion of the cost, and players in the
program, like Kansas City's Derrick Thomas, say it is a tremendous
self-esteem booster.
</P>
<P>
   A Milestone for Green
</P>
<P>
   One of the most significant achievements of this season
occurred, rather quietly, one week ago: the 50th interception by
Washington cornerback Darrell Green, a great player and one of the
league's best citizens.
</P>
<P>
   As impressive as Green's mark is, he still trails the career
interceptions leader, Paul Krause, who had 81 while playing with
Washington and Minnesota. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
